# Enquiry Management API

## Overview
This is a Node.js/Express backend API for an Enquiry Management system. It provides RESTful endpoints for managing enquiries, users, payments, tickets, and more.


## Project Structure
```
├── config/           # Configuration files (database, app config, firebase)
├── constant/         # Constants and response templates
├── controller/       # Route controllers (business logic handlers)
├── middleware/       # Express middleware (auth verification, routing)
├── models/           # Mongoose data models
├── router/           # Express route definitions
├── services/         # Business logic services
├── uploads/          # File upload directories
└── index.js          # Application entry point
```

## Tech Stack
- **Runtime**: Node.js 20
- **Framework**: Express.js
- **Database**: MongoDB (Atlas)
- **Authentication**: JWT
- **Payment**: Razorpay, CCAvenue
- **Notifications**: Firebase Cloud Messaging, Twilio, SendGrid
- **Email**: Nodemailer

## API Endpoints
- `/auth` - Authentication (login, register, OTP)
- `/user` - User management
- `/enquiry` - Enquiry CRUD operations
- `/plan` - Subscription plans
- `/followup` - Follow-up tracking
- `/notification` - Push notifications
- `/razorpay` - Payment processing
- `/coupon` - Coupon management
- `/ticket` - Support tickets
- `/leadsource` - Lead source management
- `/enquirystatus` - Enquiry status management

## Running the Application
The application runs on port 5000 and connects to MongoDB Atlas.

## Environment
- Development server: `node index.js`
- Database: MongoDB Atlas (configured in config/config.js)

